JAVA Code
Maven & Gradle
1. Developer writes .java files, Build stage converts source code into runnable package:
.java source code
      ↓
Compile
      ↓
.class files
      ↓
Package
      ↓
JAR/WAR artifact

“In Java applications, build stage is usually handled using Maven or Gradle. During build,
source code is compiled into bytecode, unit tests are executed, and deployable artifacts like JAR or WAR files are generated. 
Common commands are mvn clean package or mvn clean install. These artifacts are later containerized using Docker and deployed 
into Kubernetes or servers.”
